# Next.js Apps

- Both frontend apps use Next.js 16 App Router, React 19, TypeScript strict mode and Tailwind CSS 4.
- Use `@/*` imports inside each app according to its local `tsconfig.json`.
- Keep browser state and event handlers in client components marked with `"use client"`.
- Keep secrets, service-role clients and provider API calls in route handlers or server-only utilities.
- Preserve streaming response behavior in `apps/web/app/api/chat/route.ts` and admin AI structuring routes unless the task explicitly changes it.
- In `apps/admin`, reuse existing Supabase helpers under `lib/supabase` and `utils/supabase`; do not introduce parallel auth/session patterns.
- Validate with `pnpm --filter @fitrah/web lint`, `pnpm --filter @fitrah/admin lint`, app-specific `typecheck`, or root `pnpm lint` and `pnpm typecheck`.
